{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_019gJi63fv6qNp6QCmBT32ih","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my investigation, the failing test errors with \"register overflow\" at line 97: `class B:A static a=A def f() end static b=1 static c=A end`. The error occurs in compilation, specifically when a subclass with multiple static initializers references the inherited parent class.\n\nROOT CAUSE: `src/be_parser.c:1365-1380` (`class_static_assignment_expr`) and its interaction with `class_inherit` (`src/be_parser.c:1420-1429`). For `class B:A`, `class_inherit` calls `be_code_setsuper(finfo, e, &e1)` which runs `exp2anyreg` on the class expdesc `e` and then `free_expreg(finfo, e)` (be_code.c:858-862). After that call, the original class expdesc `e` (the one held in `class_stmt`'s stack) has been mutated and its temporary register conceptually freed, yet `class_block` keeps using that stale `e` for every subsequent `static X = …` initializer. Each `class_static_assignment_expr` does `e1 = *e` and then `be_code_member` → `package_suffix` → `exp2anyreg(c)`, which now allocates a new register on top of stack each time but never frees it (because the stale `e` still claims to be a non-ETREG / mutated type, so neither `setsfxvar`/`free_suffix` nor `free_expreg` ever reclaims the register that was bumped). Three statics in a subclass therefore leak ~3 registers per pass; multiplied across re-entries the freereg counter climbs past 255, tripping the check at `src/be_code.c:121`.\n\nLOCAL FIX: In `src/be_parser.c`, after `be_code_setsuper(...)` inside `class_inherit`, restore `e` to its original ETLOCAL form so subsequent static initializers see a clean class descriptor. Concretely, snapshot `*e` before calling `be_code_setsuper` and write it back, e.g.:\n```c\nstatic void class_inherit(bparser *parser, bexpdesc *e) {\n    if (next_type(parser) == OptColon) {\n        bexpdesc e1, save = *e;\n        scan_next_token(parser);\n        expr(parser, &e1);\n        check_var(parser, &e1);\n        be_code_setsuper(parser->finfo, e, &e1);\n        *e = save;            /* restore class expdesc */\n    }\n}\n```\nEquivalently, in `class_static_assignment_expr`, call `be_code_freeregs` to reclaim any temp register `package_suffix`/`setsfxvar` left behind, asserting `finfo->freereg` returns to its pre-statement value.\n\nGLOBAL FIX: Make register accounting symmetric and self-checking. Wrap every statement-level expression in the parser with a `freereg` save/restore (snapshot `finfo->freereg` and `finfo->nlocal` on entry, assert equality on exit in debug builds) so any helper that takes a `bexpdesc*` cannot silently leak temporaries into the caller's frame. Additionally, make `be_code_setsuper` (and other helpers that mutate caller-owned expdescs as a side effect of code emission) take a `const bexpdesc*` for the persistent operand and use a local copy internally, so callers never have to defensively snapshot. This eliminates the entire class of \"stale expdesc reused after a code helper mutated/freed it\" bugs that compounds into register overflow under benign-looking source."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1334,"cache_read_input_tokens":42738,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1334},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"81dc236a-05e9-4c2c-8ca8-54c76da08abc","uuid":"aa4e41cf-f8a9-49fa-8a1e-27f4561ed99d"}
